#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn17.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga "
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38–43. Pitusuttādichakka → pajāpati (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:0.3"
msgid "38–43. Pitusuttādichakka "
msgstr "38–43. Father, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.244, sc1
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.2"
msgid "“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya. "
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary. "

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.3"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand: "

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.4"
msgid "‘na cāyamāyasmā pitupi hetu … pe … "
msgstr "‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of their father. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.5"
msgid "(vitthāretabbaṃ) … "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 17.37.) "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.6"
msgid "bhātupi hetu … "
msgstr "brother … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.7"
msgid "bhaginiyāpi hetu … "
msgstr "sister … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.8"
msgid "puttassapi hetu … "
msgstr "son … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.9"
msgid "dhītuyāpi hetu … "
msgstr "daughter … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.10"
msgid "pajāpatiyāpi hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti. "
msgstr "wife.’ "

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.11"
msgid "Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ. "
msgstr "But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.12"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya. "
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity—bitter and harsh, an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.13"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should train like this: "

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.14"
msgid "‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let them occupy our minds.’ "

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.15"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.16"
msgid "Terasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.17"
msgid "Catuttho vaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.1"
msgid "Bhindi mūlaṃ duve dhammā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.2"
msgid "pakkantaṃ ratha mātari; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.3"
msgid "Pitā bhātā ca bhaginī, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.4"
msgid "putto dhītā pajāpatīti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.5"
msgid "Lābhasakkārasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on possessions, honor, and popularity are complete."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
